        "client_msg_id": "291A8121-EA0E-447D-BA35-12F1C83FEFEF",
        "text": "# How to play the glass bead game\n\n• #tags: #glass_bead_game #practice\n• source:\n• <https:\/\/docs.google.com\/document\/d\/1toqpJ8IcOnc-TeP_-AnGNEKz5jTIZk6OeWj2XD1REuE\/edit#|https:\/\/docs.google.com\/document\/d\/1toqpJ8IcOnc-TeP_-AnGNEKz5jTIZk6OeWj2XD1REuE\/edit#>\n• quote:\n• \"The Glass Bead Game is the gamification of the truth process. \n• The truth process is the synergy of all perspectives.\n• The GBG offers a serious play structure for truth seekers to sincerely explore topics together.\n• Players choose a topic – a bead – and take time-limited turns – 2 minutes, 1 minute, 30 seconds – to improvise an unfiltered flow of cocreation.\n•  A great turn expresses the most truth in the smallest space, and intertwines closely with the previous turn. But a great player knows when to redirect the flow, when to reflect back, when to ask questions, and when to increase or decrease the level of abstraction.\n• The aim of the game is to develop conceptual clarity, deep listening, game awareness, post-ego interactivity, and rhetorical skill to best participate in the collective intelligence of humanity.\"\n• me attention <https:\/\/weco.io\/p\/441|https:\/\/weco.io\/p\/441>\n• andy signs life <https:\/\/weco.io\/p\/805|https:\/\/weco.io\/p\/805>\n ",
